+.INDENT 0.0

+.UNINDENT
+.sp
+The chainsaw extension provides commands that are so much geared towards a
+specific use case in a specific context or environment that they are totally
+inappropriate and \fBreally dangerous\fP in other contexts.
+.sp
+The help text of each command explicitly summarizes its context of application
+and the wanted end result.

+It is recommended to run these commands with the \fBHGPLAIN\fP environment
+variable (see \%\fBhg help scripting\fP\:).

+.ft P

+packaging or deployment tools.
+.sp
+Wanted end result: local repository at the given REPO_PATH, having the
+latest changes to the given revision and with a clean working directory
+updated at the given revision.
+.sp
+chainsaw\-update pulls from one source, then updates the working directory
+to the given revision, overcoming anything that would stand in the way.

+.INDENT 0.0

+DO NOT use it for anything else than performing a series

+        <div class="section" id="chainsaw">
+          <h2>
+            <a class="toc-backref" href="#toc-entry-46">chainsaw</a>
+          </h2>
+          <p>chainsaw is a collection of single-minded and dangerous tools. (EXPERIMENTAL)</p>
+          <blockquote>&quot;Don't use a chainsaw to cut your food!&quot;</blockquote>
+          <p>
+            The chainsaw extension provides commands that are so much geared towards a
+specific use case in a specific context or environment that they are totally
+inappropriate and
+            <strong>really dangerous</strong>
+            in other contexts.
+          </p>
+          <p>The help text of each command explicitly summarizes its context of application
+and the wanted end result.</p>
+          <p>
+            It is recommended to run these commands with the
+            <tt class="docutils literal">HGPLAIN</tt>
+            environment
+variable (see
+            <a class="reference external" href="hg.1.html#scripting">
+              <tt class="docutils literal">hg help scripting</tt>
+            </a>
+            ).
+          </p>
+          <div class="section" id="commands-6">
+            <h3>Commands</h3>
+            <div class="section" id="uncategorized-commands-1">
+              <h4>Uncategorized commands</h4>
+              <div class="section" id="admin-chainsaw-update">
+                <h5>admin::chainsaw-update</h5>
+                <p>pull and update to a given revision, no matter what, (EXPERIMENTAL):</p>
+                <pre class="literal-block">hg admin::chainsaw-update [OPTION] --rev REV --source SOURCE --dest DEST</pre>
+                <p>
+                  Context of application:
+                  <em>some</em>
+                  Continuous Integration (CI) systems,
+packaging or deployment tools.
+                </p>
+                <p>Wanted end result: local repository at the given REPO_PATH, having the
+latest changes to the given revision and with a clean working directory
+updated at the given revision.</p>
+                <p>chainsaw-update pulls from one source, then updates the working directory
+to the given revision, overcoming anything that would stand in the way.</p>
+                <p>By default, it will:</p>
+                <ul class="simple">
+                  <li>
+                    clone if the local repo does not exist yet,
+                    <strong>removing any directory
+at the given path</strong>
+                    that would not be a Mercurial repository.
+The initial clone is full by default, so that clonebundles can be
+applied. Use the --initial-clone-minimal flag to avoid this.
+                  </li>
+                  <li>break locks if needed, leading to possible corruption if there
+is a concurrent write access.</li>
+                  <li>perform recovery actions if needed</li>
+                  <li>revert any local modification.</li>
+                  <li>purge unknown and ignored files.</li>
+                  <li>go as far as to reclone if everything else failed (not implemented yet).</li>
+                </ul>
+                <p>
+                  DO NOT use it for anything else than performing a series
+of unattended updates, with full exclusive repository access each time
+and without any other local work than running build scripts.
+In case the local repository is a share (see
+                  <a class="reference external" href="hg.1.html#share">
+                    <tt class="docutils literal">hg help share</tt>
+                  </a>
+                  ), exclusive
+write access to the share source is also mandatory.
+                </p>
+                <p>
+                  It is recommended to run these commands with the
+                  <tt class="docutils literal">HGPLAIN</tt>
+                  environment
+variable (see
+                  <a class="reference external" href="hg.1.html#scripting">
+                    <tt class="docutils literal">hg scripting</tt>
+                  </a>
+                  ).
+                </p>
+                <p>Motivation: in Continuous Integration and Delivery systems (CI/CD), the
+occasional remnant or bogus lock are common sources of waste of time (both
+working time and calendar time). CI/CD scripts tend to grow with counter-
+measures, often done in urgency. Also, whilst it is neat to keep
+repositories from one job to the next (especially with large
+repositories), an exceptional recloning is better than missing a release
+deadline.</p>
+                <p>Options:</p>
+                <table class="docutils option-list" frame="void" rules="none">
+                  <col class="option"/>
+                  <col class="description"/>
+                  <tbody valign="top">
+                    <tr>
+                      <td class="option-group" colspan="2">
+                        <kbd>
+                          <span class="option">--purge-unknown</span>
+                        </kbd>
+                      </td>
+                    </tr>
+                    <tr>
+                      <td/>
+                      <td>
+                        Remove unversioned files before update. Disabling this can in some cases interfere with the update.See also
+                        <a class="reference external" href="hg.1.html#purge">
+                          <tt class="docutils literal">hg purge</tt>
+                        </a>
+                        . (default: True)
+                      </td>
+                    </tr>
+                    <tr>
+                      <td class="option-group" colspan="2">
+                        <kbd>
+                          <span class="option">--purge-ignored</span>
+                        </kbd>
+                      </td>
+                    </tr>
+                    <tr>
+                      <td/>
+                      <td>
+                        Remove ignored files before update. Disable this for instance to reuse previous compiler object files. See also
+                        <a class="reference external" href="hg.1.html#purge">
+                          <tt class="docutils literal">hg purge</tt>
+                        </a>
+                        . (default: True)
+                      </td>
+                    </tr>
+                    <tr>
+                      <td class="option-group">
+                        <kbd>

+                            --rev
+                            <var>&lt;VALUE&gt;</var>
+                          </span>
+                        </kbd>
+                      </td>

+                    </tr>

+                          </span>
+                        </kbd>

+                    </tr>

+                    <tr>
+                      <td class="option-group" colspan="2">
+                        <kbd>
+                          <span class="option">--initial-clone-minimal</span>
+                        </kbd>
+                      </td>

+                    </tr>
